<!--
  Wire-spec §6 zenoh-payload-layer message-ID validator — PushBody /
  RequestBody / ResponseBody v1 allowlist (zenoh-pico
  include/zenoh-pico/protocol/definitions/message.h:27-32). Pure
  predicate over the payload-layer header byte returning true iff
  `header.mid` is a v1-recognized payload Z_MID.

  MID extraction: header & 0x1F. The payload header uses the same
  5-bit MID field as session/network/declare; upper bits host the Z
  extension-chain marker (0x80) and per-kind flags (e.g. D dropping
  bit at 0x20 for §6.1 Put, K resource-key bit at 0x80 — but Z and K
  alias on bit 7, see message.h:36 vs 38 with comments calling out
  the per-kind reinterpretation). The validator only inspects MID
  bits.

  v1 payload allowlist (per RFC §6.1 / §6.2 / §6.3 Inclusion):
    0x01  Z_PUT    (§6.1 PushBody — publish value)
    0x02  Z_DEL    (§6.1 PushBody — delete key)
    0x03  Z_QUERY  (§6.2 RequestBody — query carrier)
    0x04  Z_REPLY  (§6.3 ResponseBody — reply carrier)
    0x05  Z_ERR    (§6.3 ResponseBody — reply-channel error)

  Z_OAM (0x00) is intentionally **excluded** from the v1 payload
  allowlist: RFC §6.1 enumerates only Put/Del, §6.2 only Query,
  §6.3 only Reply/Err — payload-layer OAM is not in the mvp wire-
  spec subset. §4.2 T_OAM and §5 N_OAM remain Included for their
  respective layers (parity carrier) but the payload-layer OAM (Z_OAM
  at 0x00) lives outside the §6 mvp surface. A future Inclusion
  decision is a Phase B+ Open Question, not a v1 dispatch concern.

  Unknown payload Z_MID → false; caller maps to payload-decode error
  + session-close path. Payload runs inside an established session
  with N_DECLARE / N_PUSH / N_REQUEST / N_RESPONSE envelopes already
  validated by `network_mid_v1_valid` (R20).

  No SCE-upstream test fixture exists for payload Z_MID validation at
  vendor pin `1473f99f`; verify-codegen.sh Layer 2 (byte-golden) is
  N/A. Layer 1 (six-backend emit success) covers the RFC §5.J.4
  parity gate.
-->
<scxml xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/07/scxml"
       xmlns:sce="http://sce.dev/ext"
       xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
       xsi:schemaLocation="http://sce.dev/ext sce-forge.xsd"
       sce:kind="algorithm"
       name="payload_z_mid_v1_valid"
       version="1.0">
  <sce:signature>
    <sce:param name="header" type="uint8"/>
    <sce:return type="bool"/>
  </sce:signature>
  <sce:body>
    <sce:var name="mid" type="uint8" init="0"/>
    <sce:assign target="mid" expr="header &amp; 0x1F"/>
    <sce:if cond="mid === 0x01">
      <sce:return expr="true"/>
    </sce:if>
    <sce:if cond="mid === 0x02">
      <sce:return expr="true"/>
    </sce:if>
    <sce:if cond="mid === 0x03">
      <sce:return expr="true"/>
    </sce:if>
    <sce:if cond="mid === 0x04">
      <sce:return expr="true"/>
    </sce:if>
    <sce:if cond="mid === 0x05">
      <sce:return expr="true"/>
    </sce:if>
    <sce:return expr="false"/>
  </sce:body>
</scxml>
